		</tr>
		<tr class="twikiTableEven twikiTableRowdataBgSorted1 twikiTableRowdataBg1">
			<th bgcolor="#d8dde4" valign="top" class="twikiTableCol0 twikiFirstCol"> <font color="#252b37">enabled</font> </th>
			<td bgcolor="#f2f3f6" valign="top" class="twikiTableCol1"> <code>True</code>, <code>False</code>, <code>Ignore</code> </td>
			<td bgcolor="#f2f3f6" valign="top" class="twikiTableCol2 twikiLastCol"> This indicates whether the managed fork service is being used or not. </td>
		</tr>
		<tr class="twikiTableOdd twikiTableRowdataBgSorted0 twikiTableRowdataBg0">
			<td bgcolor="#ffffff" valign="top" class="twikiTableCol0 twikiFirstCol twikiLast"> accept_limited </td>
			<td bgcolor="#ffffff" valign="top" class="twikiTableCol1 twikiLast"> <code>True</code>, <code>False</code> </td>
			<td bgcolor="#ffffff" valign="top" class="twikiTableCol2 twikiLastCol twikiLast"> This setting is optional and will allow globus to accept limited proxies if set.  Changing this is not needed for almost all sites.  If set to <code>True</code> it will add the "accept_limited" option into <code>/etc/grid-services/jobmanager-managed-fork</code>.  If it is set to <code>False</code> or not set then that prefix will not be added. </td>
