<a name="GipResourceEntry"></a>
<h3><a name="GIP_Resource_Entry_Configuration"></a> GIP Resource Entry Configuration (ATLAS only) </h3>
<p />
If you are configuring a CE for the ATLAS VO, you must provide hardware information to advertise the queues that are available to AGIS. For each queue,  create a new <code>Resource Entry</code> section with a unique name in the following format: <code>[Resource Entry RESOURCE]</code> where RESOURCE is a globally unique resource name (it must be a <strong>globally</strong> unique name for the whole grid, not just unique to your site). The following options are required for the <code>Resource Entry</code> section and are used to generate the data required by AGIS:
<p />
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" class="twikinetWrapperTable" rules="none">
<tr class="twikinetWrapperTableRow">
<td class="twikinetWrapperTableT twikinetWrapperTableTL"></td>
